name=\"HT\" /> After that he pursued a master's degree in [[Theatre studies|Theatre and television]] from [[Punjabi University, Patiala]] before moving to [[Mumbai]] in 2001.<ref name=\"HT\" /><ref name=\"TI\" /> His father is a journalist. Singh in an interview disclosed he went to become an actor and ended up writing dialogues and scripts for comedy shows. He has worked in [[Comedy Nights with Kapil]] and [[Comedy Circus]] for a long time.<ref name=\"TI\" /> He has won 5 awards for his direction, screenwriting and stories. In 2015, he won the best screenplay award at [[PTC Punjabi Film Awards]] for writing the screenplay of [[Goreyan Nu Daffa Karo]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/punjabi/movies/news/PTC-Punjabi-Film-Awards-2015-Winners-Results/articleshow/46631183.cms|title=PTC Punjabi Film Awards 2015 Winners & Results |work=The Times of India|access-date=21 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://punjabimania.com/list-of-winners-ptc-punjabi-film-awards-2015/|title=List of Winners: PTC Punjabi Film Awards 2015 {{!}} Punjabi Mania|website=punjabimania.com|access-date=21 April 2017}}</ref> In 2016, he won 2 awards for [[Angrej]] including best screenplay and best story.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.5dariyanews.com/news/92952-No-one-makes-serious-cinema-seriously-Amberdeep-Singh|title=No one makes serious cinema seriously: Amberdeep Singh|website=5 Dariya News|access-date=17 August 2019}}</ref> In 2018, he won Best Debut Director award at [[Filmfare Punjabi Awards]] and Best Director Award at PTC Film Awards for his directorial debut [[Lahoriye]].\n\nHe has also played cameo appearances in films ''Love Punjab'', [[Sarvann]], ''Lahoriye'', [[Harjeeta]] and ''Ashke''.  He made debut as a lead Actor in [[Laung Laachi]] opposite to [[Neeru Bajwa]] followed by [[Bhajjo Veero Ve]] in 2018.\n\n== Filmography ==\n{{BLP unsourced section|date=April 2019}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Actor\n! Director\n! Dia