 rowspan=5|2017 || [[Juno Awards]] || Country Album of the Year || ''Side Effects'' || {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=4|[[Canadian Country Music Awards]] || Fans' Choice Award || {{n/a}} || {{nom}}\n|-\n| Male Artist of the Year || {{n/a}} || {{nom}}\n|-\n| Album of the Year || ''Side Effects'' || {{won}}\n|-\n| Single of the Year || \"Autograph\" || {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=4|2018 || rowspan=4|[[Canadian Country Music Awards]] || Male Artist of the Year || {{n/a}} || {{won}}\n|-\n|Fans' Choice Award || {{n/a}} || {{nom}}\n|-\n|Single of the Year || \"Side Effects\" || {{nom}}\n|-\n|Video of the Year || \"Sky Stays This Blue\" || {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=4|2019 || rowspan=4|[[Canadian Country Music Awards]] || Male Artist of the Year || {{n/a}} || {{won}}\n|-\n|Entertainer of the Year || {{n/a}} || {{won}}\n|-\n|Album of the Year || ''The Fall'' || {{nom}}\n|-\n|Fans' Choice Award || {{n/a}} || {{nom}}\n|-\n|2020 || [[Juno Awards]] || Country Album of the Year || ''The Fall'' || {{pending}}\n|}\n\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|http://www.dallassmithmusic.com/}}\n\n{{Dallas Smith}}\n{{Default (band)}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Smith, Dallas}}\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Alternative rock singers]]\n[[Category:Big Machine Records artists]]\n[[Category:Canadian alternative rock musicians]]\n[[Category:Canadian country guitarists]]\n[[Category:Canadian male guitarists]]\n[[Category:Canadian country singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Canadian male singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Juno Award for Country Album of the Year winners]]\n[[Category:Musicians from British Columbia]]\n[[Category:People from Langley, British Columbia (city)]]\n[[Category:Republic Records artists]]\n[[Category:Canadian rock singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian guitarists]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=January 2018}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Dallas Smith\n| image           = Dallas_Smith.jpg\n| birth_name = Dallas Hendry Smith\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1977|12|4}}\n| birth_place     = [[Langley, British Columbia (city)|Langley]], [[British Columbia]], Canada\n| caption         =\n| image_size      =\n| background      = solo_singer\n| origin          = [[Langley, British Columbia (city)|Langley]], British Columbia, [[Canada]]\n| instrument      =\n| genre           = {{flatlist|\n* [[Country music|Country]]\n* [[country rock]]\n* [[alternative rock]]\n* [[hard rock]]\n* [[post-grunge]]\n}}\n| occupation      = {{flatlist|\n* Singer\n* songwriter\n}}\n| years_active    = 1999\u2013present\n| label           = {{flatlist|\n* [[604 Records|604]]\n* [[Republic Nashville]]\n* [[Big Loud|Big Loud Mountain]]\n}}\n| associated_acts = [[Default (band)|Default]]\n| website         = {{official website|http://www.dallassmithmusic.com/}}\n}}\n'''Dallas Hendry Smith''' (born December 4, 1977) is a Canadian [[country music]] singer, songwriter and current lead singer for the [[hard rock]] band [[Default (band)|Default]]. He is currently signed to [[604 Records]] and [[Universal Music Canada]] and released his solo debut country album, ''[[Jumped Right In]]'', on May 22, 2012.<ref name=\"chiefmusicmanagement.com\">{{cite news|title=Dallas Smith debut country solo album \"Jumped Right In\" will be released May 22|url=http://chiefmusicmanagement.com/dallas-smith-debut-country-solo-album-jumped-right-in-will-be-released-may-22|accessdate=April 5, 2012|newspaper=Chief Music Management|date=March 28, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202230615/http://chiefmusicmanagement.com/dallas-smith-debut-country-solo-album-jumped-right-in-will-be-released-may-22|archivedate=December 2, 2013}}</ref> The album has since sold over 100,000 digital singles and generated five singles on the [[Canadian Hot 100]]. ''Jumped Right In'' was nominated as Country Album of the Year at the 2013 [[Juno Awards of 2013|Juno Awards]].\n\nAt the end of 2012, [[Mediabase]] named Dallas Smith the most played Canadian country act and number eight overall at the format.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pdf.mediabase.com/YearEnd12/YearEnd12Canada.pdf |title=Year end |publisher=pdf.mediabase.com |date=2012 |accessdate=2019-12-25}}</ref> In 2013, Smith was nominated for Male Artist of the Year, Single of the Year and Album of the Year by the [[Canadian Country Music Association]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://topcountry.ca/2013-ccma-awards-nominees-announced/|title=2013 CCMA Awards Nominees|date=2013-07-17|website=Top Country Music {{!}} Country Music News, Charts, Playlists, Videos|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-01}}</ref> Smith performed on the CCMA broadcast award ceremony, which took place on September 8, 2013.\n\nSmith co-headlined the sold out ''Boys of Fall Tour'' in November 2012 and performed at many Canadian country festivals through 2012 and 2013. In March 2013, Smith went on a sold out Canadian tour with [[Bob Seger]].\n\n==Music career==\n===Early career===\nDallas Smith always had a passion for music growing up. Some of his main influences were [[The Beatles]] and female country singers [[Reba McEntire]] and [[The Judds]]. Due to his shyness, Smith was reluctant to express his musical talent until he made the decision to face his fear and play cover songs with a band consisting of some of his friends. He signed his first record deal when he was 21.<ref>{{cite web|author=Krissie|title=Dallas Smith - December's \"Artist on the Rise|url=http://countrymusicmatters.com/2013/12/dallas-smith-decembers-artist-on-the-rise/|publisher=CMM|accessdate=2014-03-12}}</ref>\n\n===In band Default===\n{{Main|Default (band)}}\nBefore his solo career, Dallas Smith was the lead singer of multi-platinum band [[Default (band)|Default]], a [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[hard rock]]/[[post-grunge]] band from [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]]. Formed in 1999, it continued until 2013. Default's debut 2001 album, ''[[The Fallout (Default album)|The Fallout]]'', achieved instant success due to strong radio play of \"[[Wasting My Time (Default song)|Wasting My Time]]\" and \"[[Deny (Default song)|Deny]]\". In 2002 Default won the [[Juno Award]] for \"Best New Group\". On April 30, 2003 the record achieved a [[platinum album]] [[RIAA certification]], signifying a million records sold.<ref>[https://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS&artist=Default%20&format=ALBUM&go=Search&perPage=50 RIAA Database]</ref> The band also released the album ''[[Elocation]]'' (2003) which was certified gold, ''[[One Thing Remains]]'' (2005) and ''[[Comes and Goes]]'' (2009).\n\n===''Jumped Right In''===\n\n''[[Jumped Right In]]'' was released on May 22, 2012 via [[604 Records]] under the production of [[Joey Moi]].<ref name=\"chiefmusicmanagement.com\"/> The album features tracks written by Smith along with Moi, [[Rodney Clawson]], [[Craig Wiseman]], [[Dustin Lynch]], [[Chris Tompkins]], Zac Maloy, [[Chad Kroeger]] and more. It peaked at number 19 on the [[Canadian Albums Chart]] and has generated five charted singles on the [[Canadian Hot 100]]. The album was nominated for Country Album of the Year at the 2013 [[Juno Awards of 2013|Juno Awards]] and was also nominated as Album of the Year for the 2013 [[Canadian Country Music Association]] Awards. The album has sold over 100,000 digital singles to date.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.interiordailynews.com/index.php/entertainment/5575-first-country-project-from-dallas-smith-reaches-over-100000-digital-single-sales-from-album-jumped-right-in |title= First County Project |accessdate=2013-08-16 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130817073754/http://www.interiordailynews.com/index.php/entertainment/5575-first-country-project-from-dallas-smith-reaches-over-100000-digital-single-sales-from-album-jumped-right-in |archivedate=2013-08-17 }}</ref>\n\n===''Boys of Fall Tour''===\n\nIn November 2012, Smith performed on his first solo tour, co-headlining with [[Chad Brownlee]]. The tour was billed as the ''Boys of Fall Tour'' and traveled across Canada, hitting 22 cities. The tour sold out on 20 of its dates, including the Commodore Theatre in [[Vancouver|Vancouver, BC]].\n\nStemming from the success of the ''Boys of Fall Tour'', Smith and Brownlee teamed up to create the annual ''Boys of Fall Charity Golf Tournament and Concert''. The tournament took place at the Redwoods Golf Course in [[Langley, British Columbia (city)|Langley, BC]] on August 27, 2013 and was sponsored by the radio station [[CJJR-FM|JRfm]]. Proceeds from the event were donated to ''Basics for Babies'', an organization that assists families coping with the challenges of raising a young infant by providing them with needed food, formula and diapers. The tourney is currently in its fifth year and will take place Tuesday August 22, 2017.\n\n===''Tippin' Point EP''===\nIn October 2013, Smith signed with [[Republic Nashville]] and released his first American single, \"[[Tippin' Point]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://us1.campaign-archive2.com/?u=1c86c0f2d094175097ac1a0e5&id=c356a441aa&e=9c1f3d9e0c|title=BMLG Goes Pink In Support Of Breast Cancer Awareness|publisher=}}</ref> It was written by [[Brian Kelley (musician)|Brian Kelley]] and [[Tyler Hubbard]] of [[Florida Georgia Line]] with [[Jaren Johnston]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Foster|first=Ben|title=Canadian Country Star Dallas Smith Signs With Republic Nashville; Releases First Single to iTunes|url=http://www.roughstock.com/blog/canadian-country-star-dallas-smith-signs-with-republic-nashville-releases-first-single-to-itunes|accessdate=October 15, 2013|newspaper=Roughstock|date=October 10, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131018192605/http://www.roughstock.com/blog/canadian-country-star-dallas-smith-signs-with-republic-nashville-releases-first-single-to-itunes|archivedate=October 18, 2013}}</ref>\n\nSmith released an extended play, ''[[Tippin' Point (EP)|Tippin' Point]]'', on March 4, 2014 in the US and Canada. Three singles have been released from the EP so far. The title track was a top 5 single on the Canadian country radio chart and was pronounced the fastest country single to be Gold certified by [[Music Canada]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chiefmusicmanagement.com/dallas-smiths-tippin-point-the-fastest-selling-canadian-country-single/|title=Dallas Smith's \"Tippin Point\" The Fastest Selling Canadian Country Single|access-date=2014-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714143801/http://chiefmusicmanagement.com/dallas-smiths-tippin-point-the-fastest-selling-canadian-country-single/|archive-date=2014-07-14|url-status=dead}}</ref> Since then, the single has been certified Platinum in Canada and the \"Tippin' Point\" video was ranked number 1 on [[CMT (Canada)|CMT Canada]]. In the US, the song \"Tippin' Point\" was ranked number 1 on [[Sirius XM Radio|Sirius XM]]'s [[The Highway (Sirius XM)|The Highway]] Hot 45 Countdown and has sold over 120,000 singles. Smith followed up the success of the first single by releasing \"Slow Rollin'\" in March 2014. The track was a top 5 single at Canadian country radio. A third single, \"A Girl Like You\", was released in June 2014.\n\nSmith's single \"Slow Rollin'\" is performed by [[Lady Antebellum]] on the deluxe edition of their album ''[[747 (album)|747]]''.\n\n===''Lifted''===\nIn 2014, Dallas Smith entered a recording studio in [[Nashville]] to record his second full-length studio album with producer [[Joey Moi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.countryweekly.com/news/dallas-smith-returns-studio-complete-debut-country-album-tippin-point|title=Dallas Smith Returns to Studio to Complete Debut Country Album, \"Tippin' Point\"|date=25 August 2014|work=Nash Country Weekly}}</ref> The album, ''[[Lifted (Dallas Smith album)|Lifted]]'', was released on November 25, 2014. Smith released the first single off the album, \"[[Wastin' Gas]]\", on October 28, 2014 followed by album's lead track \"[[Lifted (Dallas Smith song)|Lifted]]\" and finally \"[[Cheap Seats (song)|Cheap Seats]]\".\n\n===''Side Effects'' and ''The Fall''===\nIn 2016, Dallas Smith released his third solo album ''[[Side Effects (Dallas Smith album)|Side Effects]]''. The singles released from the album included \"[[Kids with Cars]]\", \"[[One Little Kiss]]\", \"[[Autograph (Dallas Smith song)|Autograph]]\", lead title track \"[[Side Effects (Dallas Smith song)|Side Effects]]\" and \"[[Sky Stays This Blue]]\".{{Expand section|date=September 2017}} In March 2019, Smith released his EP ''[[The Fall (EP)|The Fall]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Fall - EP by Dallas Smith|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/the-fall-ep/1454055652|website=[[Apple Music]] (CA)|publisher=[[Apple Inc]]|accessdate=25 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nSmith married his longtime girlfriend Kristen in 2012 and the couple have two children together, a son and a daughter.\n\n==Discography==\n:''For discography while in band [[Default (band)|Default]], see the latter's [[Default (band)#Discography|discography]] section''\n\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Title\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Details\n!| Peak positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| [[Music recording sales certification|Certifications]]\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Canadian Albums Chart|CAN]]<br /><ref name=\"Canadian Albums\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/dallas-smith/chart-history/CNA |title=Dallas Smith Chart History (Canadian Albums) |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=January 3, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Jumped Right In]]''\n|\n* Release date: May 22, 2012\n* Label: [[604 Records|604]]\n| 19\n| \n* [[Music Canada|MC]]: Gold{{Certification Cite Ref|region=Canada|artist=Dallas Smith|accessdate=January 3, 2020|refname=\"MC certs\"}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Lifted (Dallas Smith album)|Lifted]]''\n|\n* Release date: November 25, 2014\n* Label: 604\n| 14\n| \n* MC: Gold<ref name=\"MC certs\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Side Effects (Dallas Smith album)|Side Effects]]''\n|\n* Release date: September 2, 2016\n* Label: 604\n| 7\n|\n* MC: Gold<ref name=\"MC certs\"/>\n|}\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\"| Title\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Details\n! colspan=\"4\"| Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:9em;\"| Sales\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Canadian Albums Chart|CAN]]<br /><ref name=\"Canadian Albums\" />\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Top Country Albums|US Country]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/dallas-smith/chart-history/CLP |title=Dallas Smith Chart History (Top Country Albums) |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=October 10, 2017}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Top Heatseekers|US Heat]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/dallas-smith/chart-history/TLN |title=Dallas Smith Chart History (Heatseekers Albums) |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=October 10, 2017}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Independent Albums|US Indie]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/dallas-smith/chart-history/IND |title=Dallas Smith Chart History (Independent Albums) |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=October 10, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Tippin' Point (EP)|Tippin' Point]]''\n|\n* Release date: March 4, 2014\n* Label: 604, [[Republic Nashville]]\n| 19\n| 31\n| 6\n| \u2014\n|\n* US: 2,000<ref>{{cite web|last=Bjorke|first=Matt |url=http://www.roughstock.com/blog/country-album-chart-news-the-week-of-march-12-2014-eli-young-band-10-000-towns-hits-top-of-the-charts- |title=Country Album Chart News: The Week of March 12, 2014: Eli Young Band \"10,000 Towns\" Hits Top Of The Charts |accessdate=March 28, 2014 |work=Roughstock |publisher=Cheri Media |date= March 12, 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140320121317/http://www.roughstock.com/blog/country-album-chart-news-the-week-of-march-12-2014-eli-young-band-10-000-towns-hits-top-of-the-charts- |archivedate=March 20, 2014 }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Lifted (Dallas Smith album)|Lifted]]''\n|\n* Release date: November 25, 2014\n* Label: Big Loud Mountain\n| \u2014\n| 39\n| 6\n| 47\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Kids with Cars]]''\n|\n* Release date: September 11, 2015\n* Label: Blaster Records\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Acoustic Sessions Vol. 1''\n|\n* Release date: March 2, 2018<ref>{{cite web|title=Dallas Smith To Release 'Acoustic Sessions Vol. 1'|url=http://www.iheartradio.ca/news/dallas-smith-to-release-acoustic-sessions-vol-1-1.3635491|website=[[iHeartRadio]]|accessdate=February 23, 2018|date=February 20, 2018}}</ref>\n* Label: 604\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[The Fall (EP)|The Fall]]''\n|\n* Release date: March 15, 2019\n* Label: 604\n| 91\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" style=\"font-size:8pt\"| \"\u2014\" denotes releases that did not chart\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Single\n! colspan=\"2\"| Peak chart<br />positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| [[Music recording sales certification|Certifications]]\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Sales\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Canada Country|CAN Country]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/dallas-smith/chart-history/CCW |title=Dallas Smith Chart History (Canada Country)